Class GridState

  • java.lang.Object
    • GridState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

    public class GridState
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>
    The class to represent a single state of the puzzle at any one time.
    Author:
    Dale Peters (dmp9@aber.ac.uk)

      • canMoveUp

        public boolean canMoveUp()
        Determines whether the gap (zero) can move upwards in the grid. If the zero is already in the top row of the grid, false is returned, otherwise true is returned.
        Returns:
        false if the gap (zero) can't move upwards in the grid.

      • canMoveDown

        public boolean canMoveDown()
        Determines whether the gap (zero) can move downwards in the grid. If the zero is already in the bottom row of the grid, false is returned, otherwise true is returned.
        Returns:
        false if the gap (zero) can't move downwards in the grid.

      • canMoveLeft

        public boolean canMoveLeft()

        Returns:
        false if the gap (zero) can't move leftwards in the grid.

      • canMoveRight

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Determines if the 2D array of one GridState object is equal to that of another by overriding the equals method in the Java API. It tests the deep equality of two objects, rather than the shallow equality that is tested by the equals method provided in the Object class of the Java API.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        true if the two 2D char arrays are the same.
